The paper proposes a new way of specifying finite-state protocols using scenarios and safety/liveness requirements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with formal methods and logic-based approaches to computer science. Additionally, the paper deals with distributed protocols, which suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms for solving the completion problem, which suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with state machines and transition relations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
